Joe Root has stepped down as England’s test captain, the country’s cricket board said on Friday. Root came under pressure after England slumped to a 4-0 defeat in the last Ashes series and lost 1-0 in West Indies, with former captains Michael Atherton and Nasser Hussain among many associated with the sport who said it was time for a leadership change. Thank You, @root66 — England Cricket (@englandcricket) April 15, 2022 